Delicious tacos! I ordered the shrimp, carnitas, chicken and chicken tinga tacos today and they were SO good and so fresh! It's definitely a tiny "out-of-the-way" spot, but when I got there, there was already a line of people waiting on orders- which is usually a good sign. I will absolutely be back if I'm ever in town again. So so good! And the people who work there were really friendly and accommodating. Definitely check it out if you're in the area. It's right off Broadway on a little one way street (Keap St) and it's next to impossible to find parking but your efforts will be rewarded! Only complaint was the tres leches cake :( I am super picky when it comes to tres leches and flan so I'm almost never happy when I order them from different places, and their tres leches was not so great. It definitely wasn't bad, it just wasn't really fresh, the cake itself was too rough/coarse, it randomly had canned peach chunks in the middle (? weird) and it just was NOT traditional tres leches. (Side note: I've been searching all of NY to find a great tres leches and have yet to find one...so if anyone out there can point me in the general direction of a really good tres leches PLEASE DO SO!) Thank you!
